Isiolo county governor Mohamed Kuti has been put to task by the senate ad-hoc committee on COVID 19 pandemic to come out clean over the alleged irregular leasing of intensive care unit beds from a private hospital. this follows claims by an Isiolo lobby group that some of the beds were not actually bought as the county boss purported during the launch of the ICU unit at the county referral hospital close to two months ago.the special senate committee led by Nairobi county senator johnson sakaja held separate sittings with Isiolo human rights defenders, representatives of the frontline health workers working at isiolo county referral hospital and finally the county government administration led by governor Kuti before visiting the facility to inspect the beds in question.